# AutoForge

AI multi-agent project generation framework. 6 agents build complete projects from natural language descriptions.

## Commands

```bash
./setup.sh                              # Setup (macOS/Linux)
setup.bat                               # Setup (Windows)
source .venv/bin/activate               # Activate venv
python forge.py "project description"   # Generate project
python forge.py --budget 5.00 "desc"    # With budget limit
python forge.py --status                # Show projects
python forge.py --resume                # Resume interrupted run
python tests/smoke_test.py              # Run 31-check smoke test
python forge.py daemon start            # Start 24/7 daemon
python forge.py queue "description"     # Add to build queue
python forge.py projects                # List all projects
python forge.py deploy <project_id>     # Show deploy guide
```

## Architecture

**Pipeline:** SPEC → BUILD → VERIFY → REFACTOR → DELIVER

**Agents:** Director (Opus), Architect (Opus), Builder (Sonnet, parallel), Reviewer (Sonnet), Tester (Sonnet), Gardener (Sonnet)

## Key Files

- `forge.py` — CLI entry point
- `engine/orchestrator.py` — 5-phase pipeline controller
- `engine/config.py` — ForgeConfig dataclass (models, budget, paths)
- `engine/llm_router.py` — LLM routing (Opus/Sonnet) + budget enforcement
- `engine/agent_base.py` — Agentic tool-use loop base class
- `engine/task_dag.py` — Task dependency graph + scheduler
- `engine/lock_manager.py` — Cross-platform atomic task locking
- `engine/git_manager.py` — Git worktree isolation for parallel builders
- `engine/sandbox.py` — Subprocess + Docker sandbox
- `engine/project_registry.py` — SQLite multi-project management (daemon mode)
- `engine/daemon.py` — 24/7 daemon controller
- `engine/deploy_guide.py` — Vercel deployment guide generator
- `engine/channels/` — Input channels (Telegram bot, webhook API)
- `engine/agents/` — 6 agent implementations
- `constitution/` — Agent behavior rules (editable markdown)
- `constitution/agents/*.md` — Per-agent system prompts
- `constitution/workflows/*.md` — Phase definitions
- `services/` — systemd + launchd service configs

## Coding Standards

- Python 3.11+ with `from __future__ import annotations`
- Fully async (`async/await`, `asyncio`)
- Type hints on all function signatures
- `pathlib.Path` for file paths (never string concatenation)
- `rich` library for terminal output
- Cross-platform (`sys.platform` checks, `tempfile` for temp dirs)
- Path traversal prevention in agent file operations
- Budget tracking on every LLM call via `config.record_usage()`
- Test changes with `python tests/smoke_test.py` before committing
